bq_schema.description: A JSON string containing any payload properties not present in the schema
bq_schema.name: additional_properties

fields.description: The optional Android specific SDK version of the software running on this hardware device.
fields.name: android_sdk_version

fields.description: The build identifier generated by the CI system (e.g. "1234/A"). For language bindings that provide automatic detection for this value, (e.g. Android/Kotlin), in the unlikely event that the build identifier can not be retrieved from the OS, it is set to "inaccessible". For other language bindings, if the value was not provided through configuration, this metric gets set to `Unknown`.
fields.name: app_build

fields.description: The channel the application is being distributed on.
fields.name: app_channel

fields.description: The user visible version string (e.g. "1.0.3").  In the unlikely event that the display version can not be retrieved, it is set to "inaccessible".
fields.name: app_display_version

fields.description: The architecture of the device, (e.g. "arm", "x86").
fields.name: architecture

fields.description: A UUID uniquely identifying the client.
fields.name: client_id

fields.description: The manufacturer of the device the application is running on. Not set if the device manufacturer can't be determined (e.g. on Desktop).
fields.name: device_manufacturer

fields.description: The model of the device the application is running on. On Android, this is Build.MODEL, the user-visible marketing name, like "Pixel 2 XL". Not set if the device model can't be determined (e.g. on Desktop).
fields.name: device_model

fields.description: The date of the first run of the application.
fields.name: first_run_date

fields.description: The locale of the application during initialization (e.g. "es-ES"). If the locale can't be determined on the system, the value is ["und"](https://unicode.org/reports/tr35/#Unknown_or_Invalid_Identifiers), to indicate "undetermined".
fields.name: locale

fields.description: The name of the operating system. Possible values: Android, iOS, Linux, Darwin, Windows, FreeBSD, NetBSD, OpenBSD, Solaris, unknown
fields.name: os

fields.description: The user-visible version of the operating system (e.g. "1.2.3"). If the version detection fails, this metric gets set to `Unknown`.
fields.name: os_version

fields.description: The version of the Glean SDK
fields.name: telemetry_sdk_build

bq_schema.description: The document ID specified in the URI when the client sent this message
bq_schema.name: document_id

fields.description: Results of a geographic lookup based on the client's IP address
An ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code
fields.name: country

fields.description: The specific geo database version used for this lookup
fields.name: db_version

fields.description: First major country subdivision, typically a state, province, or county
fields.name: subdivision1

fields.description: Second major country subdivision; not applicable for most countries
fields.name: subdivision2
geo

fields.description: Headers included in the client's HTTP request
Date HTTP header
fields.name: date

fields.description: DNT (Do Not Track) HTTP header
fields.name: dnt

fields.description: X-Debug-Id HTTP header
fields.name: x_debug_id

fields.description: X-PingSender-Version HTTP header
fields.name: x_pingsender_version

fields.description: X-Source-Tags HTTP header
fields.name: x_source_tags
header

fields.description: Results of ISP lookup based on the client's IP address
The specific geo ISP database version used for this lookup
fields.name: db_version

fields.description: The name of the ISP associated with the client's IP address
fields.name: name

fields.description: The name of a specific business entity associated with the client's IP address when available; otherwise the ISP name
fields.name: organization
isp

fields.description: Parsed components of the client's user agent string
fields.name: user_agent

fields.description:
Counts the number of times we encountered an invalid timezone offset
when trying to get the current time.
A timezone offset is invalid if it is outside [-24h, +24h].
If invalid a UTC offset is used (+0h).
fields.name: glean_time_invalid_timezone_offset

fields.description:
The number of pings deleted after the quota
for the size of the pending pings directory or number of files is hit.
Since quota is only calculated for the pending pings directory,
and deletion request ping live in a different directory,
deletion request pings are never deleted.
fields.name: glean_upload_deleted_pings_after_quota_hit

fields.description:
The total number of pending pings at startup.
This does not include deletion-request pings.
fields.name: glean_upload_pending_pings

fields.description: This metric counts how many times a dirty bit was detected when starting the Glean SDK, on Android. This dirty bit is set to `true` when Android's lifecycle `ON_START` is hit and flipped back to false on `ON_STOP`. When an application is force-closed, it might not get the `ON_STOP` and so the value would stay `true`. The next time Glean starts, it will increment this counter.
fields.name: glean_validation_app_forceclosed_count

fields.description: The number of baseline pings sent during the lifetime of this metrics ping.

fields.description:
Measures the current open tab count as the application
goes to background. Each background event adds to this
metric, making it the cumulative sum of all open tabs
when the app goes to background during the period of
time covered by a single metrics ping. This can be
divided by the number of baseline pings with
`ping_info.reason="inactive"` from the `start_time` to
the `end_time` of the metrics ping to determine the
average open tabs per foreground "session".
fields.name: tabs_cumulative_count

fields.description:

This includes failures for all ping types,
though the counts appear in the next successfully sent `metrics` ping.
fields.name: glean_upload_ping_upload_failure

fields.description:
A count of the pings submitted, by ping type.

This metric appears in both the metrics and baseline pings.

- On the metrics ping, the counts include the number of pings sent since
  the last metrics ping (including the last metrics ping)
- On the baseline ping, the counts include the number of pings send since
  the last baseline ping (including the last baseline ping)
fields.name: glean_validation_pings_submitted

fields.description:
The labels for this counter are `{search-engine-name}.{source}`

If the search engine is bundled with Firefox-iOS, then
`search-engine-name` will be the name of the search engine. If
it is a custom search engine, the value will be `custom`.

The value of `source` will reflect the source from which the
search started.  One of:
* quicksearch
* suggestion
* actionbar
fields.name: search_counts

fields.description: Records the type of interaction a user has on SERP pages.

appropriate label when either a normal or private tab

fields.description:

fields.description:
The URL scheme of the mail client that the user wants to use
for `mailto:` links. It is used to measure usage of this
feature, to see how effective feature promotion campaigns are
and to report back to third-party mail clients what percentage
of users is using their client.
fields.name: preferences_mail_client

fields.description:
The name of the view that the user wants to see on new tabs.
For example History, Homepage or Blank. It is used to measure
usage of this feature, to see how effective feature promotion
campaigns are and to establish a baseline number for when we
introduce the new Activity Stream features.
fields.name: preferences_new_tab_experience

fields.description:
The default search engine identifier if the search engine is
pre-loaded with Firefox-iOS.  If it's a custom search engine,
then the value will be 'custom'.
fields.name: search_default_engine

fields.description:

fields.description:

fields.name: theme_name

fields.description:

tracking-protection that is enabled. One of:
* basic
* strict
fields.name: tracking_protection_strength
